  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2022-02-25",
    "date": "2022-03-07T13:44:29Z",
    "text": "Supporting Americans with Lower Taxes Act or the SALT Act\n\nThis bill modifies the limitation on the tax deduction for certain state, local, and foreign real and personal property taxes. Specifically, the bill denies a tax deduction for foreign real property taxes to any individual taxpayer with an adjusted gross income that equals or exceeds $400,000. It also limits the deduction for the aggregate amount of other state and local taxes and sales taxes for such taxpayers to $60,000 in a taxable year.\n\nThe bill transfers revenues from this bill to a Medicare Vision and Hearing Trust Fund to provide vision and hearing benefits under the Medicare program."
  },
